The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, November 25, 2002 				 Voice against violence
																								Today is an important date on the world calendar: it is the International Day Protesting Violence Against Women. Beginning today, Swayam, a city-based NGO working against violence on women, will observe the International Fortnight Protesting Violence against Women with a series of programmes to sensitise people on this burning issue. The series of programmes include a poster exhibition: Half the Sky, to be inaugurated today at Park Circus Maidan at 2 pm. This will be followed by Jhankar  Breaking the Silence Surrounding Violence  a music concert by school bands on November 30 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar, 3 pm. Pratibimb  Reflections of Reality  a film festival on womens issues will be held between December 2 and 5 and December 7 at Max Mueller Bhavan and The Seagull Foundation for the Arts. On December 8, a rally on wheels: Sankalp  Towards a Violence-free World  will begin from Shahid Minar at 9.30 am. Also, workshops with college students and rural women of East Midnapore, Antara Gram, Baruipur, Pailan, Bede Bustee (Brace Bridge) involved in self-help groups, story sharing session et al are on the cards.The progranmme concludes on December 10, International Human Rights Day.
